{
  "doc_id": "19977",
  "text": "The presence of genes encoding TEM, SHV, OXA, CTX-M, and CMY type ␤-lactamases was studied by specific PCRs [CITATION_1] . All obtained amplicons were sequenced on both strands, and sequences were compared with those included in the GenBank database and at the Lahey Clinic website (http://www.lahey.org /Studies/) to identify the ␤-lactamase genes.",
